comments_data.body:
I've edited the post above to include the relevant info from the crash log.
this seems a bit similar to #10234

we've upgraded from old stable 3rd version directly to 6.2.6 (completely new clean instance based on latest centos7), it's a clean instance without rdb or something just for caching. problem appeared several times after about 4-6 hours of work (so any usual test could not find any problem) on 2 different instances started in one time with more or less equal load. difference in crash time was around 3 minutes between them. i'll try to mirror requests from stable old redis version to make it even more reproducible.

@ddrdikko Can you share the systemd unit file used to start Redis? Is it possible that you specify some systemd-level memory limit?

also, maybe the system's `overcommit_memory` is disabled, and some other process allocated big amounts of memory?

Overcommit_memory was set to 2, but there were no other processes. it's a fresh clean vm dedicated only to this redis instance.
According to monitoring, there was 12-13Gb free at the moment of crash.

unit file, no limits specified by me anywhere.
```
[Unit]
Description=Redis persistent key-value database
After=network.target
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/redis-server /etc/redis/redis.conf --daemonize no --supervised systemd
ExecStop=/usr/libexec/redis-shutdown
Type=notify
User=redis
Group=redis
RuntimeDirectory=redis
RuntimeDirectoryMode=0755

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

```

i'll try to look at vm.max_map_count value increasing.

upd:
in crash report there was 4084 memory fragments logged. it's close to 4096 possible limit somewhere.

and from ipcs -l output i've got

------ Shared Memory Limits --------
**max number of segments = 4096**
max seg size (kbytes) = 67108864
max total shared memory (kbytes) = 17179869184
min seg size (bytes) = 1

can it be the cause ?

@oranagra setting **kernel.shmmni** = 32768 solved my issue. 1 week of tests was done without any issues.
maybe this sould be included in administrators/installation guide.
